    <header>
      <h1>Reading Group: Around the Classical and Quantum PCP</h1>
      <p><strong>When:</strong> 4:30pm-7:30pm, Thursdays (Winter 2025)</p>
      <p><strong>Where:</strong> SC 0216, University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign</p>
      <p><strong>Organizers:</strong> <a href="https://granha.github.io"> Fernando Granha Jeronimo </a> </p> 
    </header>
    <main>
      <section>
	<h2> Overview </h2>
        <p>
          Welcome to our reading group dedicated to a broad exploration around Classical and Quantum PCPs (Probabilistically Checkable Proofs).
        </p>	
        <img src="img_pcp.jpg" alt="Classical and Quantum PCP visualization">
      </section>
      <section>
	<h2> Tentative Format</h2>
	We can have usual ~1 hour talks, or, ideally, more intense (and fun ;) ~3 hours gatherings depending on the speaker interests.
	<ul>
	  <li> First Part (~1 hour): general presentation about the work with context, motivation, and overview of technical results possibly with some simpler proofs.</li>
	  <li> Break (~30 minutes): recharge and socialize. </li>
	  <li> Second Part (~1 hour + x minutes): present (some of) the technical part and proofs in more detail.</li>
	  <li> Final Part (~30- x minutes): more questions, free speculations, and socialization.</li> 
	</ul>
      </section>
      <section>
	<h2> A List of Papers </h2>
        <p>
	  You are welcome to present any paper broadly related to our main topic.
        </p>

	<ul>
	  <li> <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1309.7495">The Quantum PCP Conjecture</a> survey by Aharonov, Arad, Vidick </li>
	  <li> <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.16475">Circuit-to-Hamiltonian from tensor networks and fault tolerance</a> by Anshu, Breuckmann, Nguyen</li>
	  <li> <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2402.07476">Expansion of higher-dimensional cubical complexes with application to quantum locally testable codes</a> by Dinur, Lin, Vidick</li>	  
	</ul>

	<ul>
	  <li> <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2407.12762">Quasi-Linear Size PCPs with Small Soundness from HDX</a> by Bafna, Minzer, Vyas</li>
	</ul>
      </section>      
